RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 59. Maiden Claiming Purse 7900. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUGAR SHANE Led on the rail from the outset, maintained advantage until being joined at the quarter pole, brushed off foe inside the quarter pole, to the wire willingly. CLASSIC CALIFORNIA Pressed two wide into first turn, joined rival at the quarter pole, shaken off at the eighth pole, tried lane, second best. DYNAMIC WOMAN Tucked in from outer draw to sit in the second flight on the rail, stalked inside throughout, made mild progress in behind top duo around the turn, finished evenly. OJO FELIZ Settled in rear, advanced up rail at the three-eighths, further gained from the quarter to the eighth pole but was unable to fully sustain bid. MOBILEAGILEHOSTILE Moved four wide around the first bend off the pace, stymied in place while three wide into the second turn, never factored. WE WANT ANOTHER Traveled three wide into the first turn, called upon at the three-eighths but showed no improve, between rivals on the second turn, tired into and down the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Sugar Shane
ENTRY.COMMENT: To lead rail, joined 1/4, brushed off foe 1/8, willingly

ENTRY.NAME: Ojo Feliz
ENTRY.COMMENT: In rear, adv rail 3/8, further gain 1/4 to 1/8, unable to sustain

ENTRY.NAME: Classic California
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w first, press pace, adjoined outer 1/4, shook off 1/8, 2nd best

ENTRY.NAME: We Want Another
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w first, ask 3/8 w no improve, btwn turn, tired lane

ENTRY.NAME: Mobileagilehostile
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4w first, 3w second, never a factor

ENTRY.NAME: Dynamic Woman
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2nd flight tucked in, stalked ins, mild progress btwn, evenly str

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 8100. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE OCTOBER 1, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FLYUNDERTHEGRAYDAR Stumbled to knees at the break but quickly recovered to vie for the lead, held the rail in a duel lasting throughout the backside, shook free from field at the quarter pole, opened up enough to hold sway through the stretch. ROCKED Settled inside in the second flight, tracked well off the pace, commenced at the three-eighths pole by swinging three wide for clean air, picked up strongly on the wrong lead through the stretch, ran out of time. LIL LATIGO Moved two wide into the first turn, pinched out of a spot on the first turn and drifted out, advanced inside of rivals into the turn but simply had too much to do. EDINBURGH EXPRESS Joined two wide into the first turn and began a duel that lasted until backing out at the quarter pole, finished evenly. TWO SOCKS MAC Hopped at the break, had no speed early, lagged far behind until the eighth pole when showing strong progress to the wire while passing tiring. KING LEBRON Moved three wide into the first turn, carried out by troubled rival, continued to move outside in a line of three three wide, flattened out down the stretch. BECOME AN INSIDER Had no foot early and was well off the pace, attempted to improved along the rail at the quarter pole, failed to gain. BLUE GESSAMI Four to three wide into the first turn, backed out between horses at the three-eighths, five path into the lane, tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Become an Insider
ENTRY.COMMENT: Well off, attempt to improve 1/4, failed to gain

ENTRY.NAME: Flyunderthegraydar
ENTRY.COMMENT: Stumble brk, duel backside, shook free 1/4, held sway

ENTRY.NAME: Rocked
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: Ins 2nd flight, track well off, commence 3w 3/8, flew, not enough

ENTRY.NAME: Lil Latigo
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w, pinch 1st, drift out, adv inner turn, too much to do

ENTRY.NAME: Two Socks Mac
ENTRY.COMMENT: Hop break, lagged far behind, strong progress 1/8 to wire

ENTRY.NAME: Edinburgh Express
ENTRY.COMMENT: 2w 1st, duel outs, back out 1/4, evenly home

ENTRY.NAME: King Lebron
ENTRY.COMMENT: 3w, carried first, outer 3w, flattened out

ENTRY.NAME: Blue Gessami
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4-3w first, back out 3/8ths btwn, 5p str, tired lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 3 4F Dirt CR: 61. Maiden Special Weight Purse 8500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BAKERSFIELD BABE Hustled to the lead between horses, moved to the rail with advantage, opened up into the turn and distanced the field. LUCKY LUPE Tucked in right behind leaders, moved up in the four path on the turn, shift to the six path into the lane, got up for place. GATO SICILIANO Broke inwards, pressed three wide, moved to the rail on the turn, no extra late, nipped for place. WEST COAST ANDY Inside off the pace, evenly on turn, mildly through the stretch. PIRATE MISCHIEF Pinched between shortly after the break, between horses second flight, no improve in heat of battle, evenly home. QUEEN MYSTIC Outpaced while widest, no menace. A RIDERS OBJECTION WAS LODGED FROM #4 PIRATE MISCHIEF AGAINST #6 GATO SICILIANO FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE SHORTLY AFTER THE START. THE STEWARDS RULED IN FAVOR OF #4 PIRATE MISCHIEF AND DISQUALIFIED #6 GATO SICILIANO FROM THIRD TO FIFTH.

ENTRY.NAME: West Coast Andy
ENTRY.COMMENT: Inside off pace, evenly turn, mildly stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Lucky Lupe
ENTRY.OWNER: Di Filippo Jo Ann and Ortega Nathaniel F
ENTRY.COMMENT: Inside tucked in behind, move up 4p turn, 6p lane, up for place

ENTRY.NAME: Pirate Mischief
ENTRY.COMMENT: Pinch btwn after break, btwn 2nd flight, no improve, evenly

ENTRY.NAME: Bakersfield Babe
ENTRY.COMMENT: Hustled to lead, rail, opened up turn, distanced field

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Gato Siciliano
ENTRY.COMMENT: Brk in, 3w press, move to rail turn, no extra, nipped place

ENTRY.NAME: Queen Mystic
ENTRY.COMMENT: Outpaced while widest, no menace

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 8100. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE APRIL 1, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAYNESPUN Dueled outside of a rival from the outset, kept to task throughout and into the turn, in a dogfight with nagging rival through the lane, got up in the dying strides. BAD KARMA Worked hard to enforce positioning along the rail, maintained in duel inside throughout, battled through the lane with same opponent, outfinished in the final yards. SHAMAN'S PRODIGY Settled well off the pace on the rail, presented some mild foot into the turn and down the stretch to get up for show. TOTHEMOONANDBACK Stalked dueling leaders from the outset three wide, stayed in touch with foes to the eighth pole, gave way and tired lane. MY FUNNY GAL Settled off the pace two wide, failed to improve. CHRISTA SLEW Toss head around at the break, moved well off the early speed, never a menace. ELEMENTAL Broke in stride, got in tight and in trouble into the first turn, became far detached from the field, never became involved, eased home.

ENTRY.COMMENT: Well off on rail, mild advance turn to stretch, up for show

ENTRY.COMMENT: Awkward break, well off, no menace

ENTRY.COMMENT: Duel ins, maintained, battle lane, outfinished final yards

ENTRY.COMMENT: Duel outs throughout, in fight lane, up in dying strides

ENTRY.COMMENT: Stalk 3w, in touch to 1/8, gave way

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RILLITO RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 87. Claiming Purse 8450. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND OLDER WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON THREE RACES SINCE APRIL 1, 2022. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOTERO Let the hard dueling leaders go and led a race of his own into the backstretch, topped the second flight up the backstretch, commenced move at the five-sixteenths pole by swinging to the three path, continued surged through the stretch, up inside the final fifty yards. GONE SOMEWHERE Hard sent to duel on the outside of a rival, quarter horsed up the backstretch to an extensive lead, moved to a clear advantage at the eighth pole, overtaken inside the sixteenth, no extra. LOW DOSE Hustled to lead inside of a rival, opened up a hefty advantage with dueling foe up the backstretch, stayed in touch despite behind overtaken at the eighth pole, held enough for show. PALACE PRINCE Bobbled at the break, tucked in in the rear, moved up at the five-sixteenths and continued to progress at the quarter pole, finished up willingly. GUARDING ELK CAMP Well off the pace two wide, asked at the quarter pole but idled in the four path on the second turn, tired. FULL DRAW Broke a touch slow, forced four wide into the first turn, maintained position backside, moved to the rail at the quarter pole, never picked up stride. PLATINUM EQUITY Traveled three wide into the first turn, dropped back at the three-eighths pole, failed to improve.

ENTRY.NAME: Botero
ENTRY.COMMENT: top 2nd flight, let leaders go, mv 5/16, 3p turn, surge, up late

ENTRY.OWNER: Tijuana Racing Stables Tenenbaum Jeffrey and Bloom Jeffrey
ENTRY.COMMENT: Bobble brk, tucked in rear, move 5/16, progress 1/4, willingly
